# Buffer Overflow Exercises

## Overview
This directory contains my work on understanding and exploiting buffer overflows, as part of a course assignment.

## My Contributions
- **Developed two Python scripts** for testing and analysis.
- **Wrote two assembly files** to demonstrate my approach and learning process.
## Context
- The original C program (`hackme.c`) was provided by the professor and is not included in this repository.
- The solution files are also not published here, as they were not my own creation.
## Current Status
The Python and assembly files represent different stages of my learning and are not yet fully functional.
I plan to refine and fix them in a future commit.

## Purpose
This directory documents my progress and understanding of buffer overflows,
from initial experiments to more advanced attempts.